EU Leaders Agree More Needed to Be Done on Debt Crisis

-- B y   J a m e s   G .   N e u g e r
-- 
2011-10-23T19:57:26Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-23/eu-leaders-agree-more-needed-to-be-done-on-debt-crisis.html
Euro-area governments agreed to take
further steps to combat the debt crisis, European Union
President  Herman Van Rompuy  said.  “The immediate economic challenges are so serious that we
must do more,”  Van Rompuy  told reporters after a euro-area
summit in Brussels today. “We are determined to take all
necessary measures and actions needed to ensure the stability of
the euro area.”  He said the euro zone is considering “several options” to
strengthen the firewall against contagion.   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James G. Neuger at 
 jneuger@bloomberg.net  